post_text:
To the Forsan ISD Students and Parents,

Governor Greg Abbott announced today that schools in Texas would not reopen their school facilities for this current school year but would continue the education of our students through distance learning. Although this saddens us, his goal of keeping us all safe makes this decision understandable. We will soon announce plans for graduation of our 2020 Senior class. We will gradually make other announcements related to end-of-school activities. But first, there are about five weeks of school remaining. We want all of our students to reach their full potential and to accomplish their goals. A serious approach to school work and a “finish strong” attitude are both important in these last few weeks. Thank you each for making this new environment work.

“Dare to be Great!”

Randy Johnson

Superintendent

Forsan ISD

#COVID19 lives on droplets in the lungs of people with the virus, even if they don’t have symptoms. When infected people breathe, the virus enters the air. If you can’t #StayHome, wear a mask/scarf/bandana, stay 6 feet apart, and wash your hands. #DontGoViral

Daily Update for Thursday, 3/19/2020:

The governor has given an executive order to close schools starting tomorrow night at midnight through April 3. Closing school does not mean that we don't offer instruction or that staff can't come into the building. We'll continue as we have this week through April 3. Meals will be provided at the same locations and times.

Packet Pick-Up/Drop-Off will be on Monday at the following times. You will drop-off your completed packet and pick-up your new one.

7:30 AM - 8:30 AM
11:00 AM - 1:00 PM
3:00 PM - 4:00 PM

Thank you for all of your hard work parents! Please let the teacher know if your student needs help, they will be excited to hear from you!

P.S. Stay tuned for a new video featuring your teachers to drop around 3 PM tomorrow!

Daily Update for Wednesday, 3/18/2020

The packet pick-up line was a huge success today! Thank you to all the parents for driving out and picking up the packets. We appreciate your commitment to the success of your students and were excited to see each and every one of you! Even though we sadly cannot be at school together, we still must take attendance and grades and this is a great first step. If you have any questions about your student's classwork, please do not hesitate to contact your teacher, as they would be more than happy to help.

Forsan Elementary Families: While we are sad that we are not at school, but we will be waiting and ready with your packets tomorrow! If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact your teacher or the elementary front office.

Thanks!

post_text: This evening, Forsan ISD administrators were made aware of a high school student who apparently made a series of verbal threats to the safety of students. Statements were made to other students that they should wear blue tomorrow to school in order to be safe. This was interpreted as a threat and safety protocols were immediately followed including notifying the Howard County Sheriff’s office. The sheriff’s office responded this evening and took the student into custody. Thanks go out to the students who reported this, the teachers and parents who made sure that administrators were made aware and to the Howard County Sheriff’s office for their quick response.

post_text:
Forsan ISD is in the process of establishing this year’s District Improvement Team. This committee will be made up of 2 parents, 2 community members, 2 business members, and various staff. The committee is challenged annually with providing feedback to the district-level administration. There will be at least two meetings including one in October and one in February. Meetings are normally held at 4 pm in the Board Room. (Campus level committees will also be forming soon.)
If you are interested in serving on this committee, please email your name, contact information, and some basic facts about your connection to the community/school to Mr. Randy Johnson at rsjohnso@forsan.esc18.net. Members will be selected that fit the categories listed above. Forsan ISD is blessed with a supportive community. We look forward to working together. Thank you.

post_text: We love you, Mrs. Thixton! Thank you for 50 years of dedication to students!
shared_text:
KBest Media
April 30, 2019 at 5:04 PM ·

Legend in Education Retires after 50 years of service in Forsan.

Earlier today, Forsan ISD celebrated the retirement of Eunice Thixton, who has served 50 outstanding years in education.

Randy Johnson, Forsan Superintendent, told KBest News that Thixton has filled so many important roles by taking care of children, ensuring their safety, and ensuring that they were getting what they needed out of the education system. He stated that she is an asset to not only Forsan ISD, but also to their community.
